  "texts": [
    "Among them, Haque et al. (2022) and Taecharungroj (2023) performed topic modeling using the Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA) technique (Blei et al. 2003), aiming to discover popular topics in ChatGPT-related tweets.",
    "Leiter et al. (2023) used a roBERTa-based model fine-tuned for tweet topic classification to classify tweets into pre-determined topics for analysis.",
    "To examine the public sentiment toward ChatGPT, Tounsi et al. (2023) and Korkmaz et al.",
    "(2023) applied lexicon-or rule-based models to obtain sentiment scores, while Haque et al. (2022) performed per-topic sentiment analysis by manually labeling the tweets.",
    "Most similar to our study, Leiter et al. (2023) used a Transformer-based model fine-tuned for sentiment analysis to classify each tweet as positive, negative, or neutral."
  ],
